## Safe Area

Always use `SafeAreaView` from `react-native-safe-area-context`.
Never hardcode padding for notch or status bar.

```tsx
import { SafeAreaView } from 'react-native-safe-area-context';

<SafeAreaView style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: Colors.backgroundWhite }}>
  {/* screen content */}
</SafeAreaView>
```

---

## Styling Rules

Use NativeWind `className` for all styling. Never use `StyleSheet.create()` or inline styles.

Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to conditionally combine classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<Text className={cn('text-base font-medium text-black', task.completed && 'line-through text-muted')} />
```

Map design tokens to Tailwind classes:

```
#242424  → bg-primary / text-primary
#fffce3  → bg-cream
#fafafa  → bg-offwhite
#606060  → text-text-secondary
#757575  → text-text-muted
#ffffff  → bg-white / text-white
#6270f0  → text-accent-blue / bg-accent-blue
#ffe600  → text-accent-yellow
#e9ffe3  → bg-category-sport
#e3e6ff  → bg-category-habits
```

Border radius:
```
rounded-[30px]   ← screen frames
rounded-[45px]   ← task list container
rounded-2xl      ← task item cards (16px)
rounded-full     ← buttons, tab bar, pill shapes
rounded-[26px]   ← small add buttons
```

